{
  "stem": "20616.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And after that, we landed in Hoboken and some friends who had been there a few months earlier also from Wiesbaden came.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Actually, the lady was a very good friend of my mother's.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they came and there was an American friend also who came.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I remember we landed in Hoboken next to the old Leviathan-- there was a rusty old wreck.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was an old ship that was called a different name but it wasn't used anymore.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It used to be the pride of the-- it was a reparation from World War I.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE], no not the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It had some sort of a name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we went over the gangplank and then American friend, the first question-- the first thing I heard was, how do you like America [LAUGHS] as I walked over the gangplank.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I said, just fine, just fine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then they took me to a drugstore, where I had the-- I was supposed to try an ice cream soda.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was a very seedy-- looking drugstore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They said, that's the national drink.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I thought it was the most horrible drink imaginable.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But of course, they meant well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I said, oh, it was delicious.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And that was my first day coming into Hoboken.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we settled in Washington Heights, in New York, which was more or less the German-- most of the German refugees settled there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was inexpensive, it was a relatively decent neighborhood at that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we had a room-- they rented a room for us in a boarding house where the three of us lived in one room for the first six months or so.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And every room was occupied by a refugee looking for work.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
